text: Northeast Investigator Shoal ( ; ), also marked as Investigator Northeast Shoal on some nautical charts, is a shoal in the Spratly group of islands in South China sea. The submerged coral atoll is located 32 nautical miles from at 9° 10' N, 116° 28' E. A small feature with an area of just 2 square kilometres, the shoal has a few rocks at the western edge that are just about visible at high water. ==References== Category:Shoals of the Spratly Islands Category:Reefs of China Category:Reefs of the Philippines Category:Reefs of Taiwan Category:Reefs of Vietnam Category:Disputed reefs
